---
import RadialMotif from './RadialMotif.astro';
---

<section id="wellbeing" class="section wellbeing" aria-labelledby="wellbeing-title">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-index reveal">
      <span>05</span><i aria-hidden="true"></i><span>Giving and health</span>
    </div>
    <div class="wellbeing-grid">
      <div class="wellbeing-heading" data-reveal-group>
        <p class="eyebrow reveal">What giving does to the giver</p>
        <h2 id="wellbeing-title" class="t-section font-display reveal">Generosity, studied as a variable.</h2>
        <p class="reveal">
          Several research lines examine associations between volunteering, civic participation, social perception, health, and wellbeing. The populations and methods differ, so the findings are presented separately.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="wellbeing-visual reveal"><RadialMotif variant="rosette" /></div>
    </div>

    <article class="finding-feature reveal">
      <div>
        <span class="finding-number font-display">R34</span>
        <p>NIH funding mechanism</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Featured research</p>
        <h3 class="font-display">TUNE In</h3>
        <p>
          Training to Understand and Navigate Emotions and Interactions is a structured social-engagement intervention that examines whether volunteering can improve social functioning in young adults on the autism spectrum.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <div class="findings-list" data-reveal-group>
      <article class="reveal">
        <span>2019, 2023</span>
        <h3>Volunteering and later-life wellbeing</h3>
        <p>Longitudinal studies examine wellbeing among aging adults and what happens when older adults retire from volunteering.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="reveal">
        <span>2021</span>
        <h3>The Good-looking Giver Effect</h3>
        <p>Research with Sara Konrath tests whether people who give and volunteer are perceived as more attractive by others.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="reveal">
        <span>Current research</span>
        <h3>Voting and mortality risk</h3>
        <p>This later research thread asks whether voting predicts lower mortality risk and whether it should be considered a social determinant of health.</p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <p class="course-note reveal">
      <strong>Open course:</strong> <cite>The Science of Generosity: Do Good, Feel Good</cite>, offered through Penn on edX.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
